
>>>>>>> COMMANDS

alias: subsitute lengthy commands with shorter ones

-p 	prints out list of aliases


cat : join files and output to stdout

-n 	number lines, useful to show which line of code is a particular statement on.


cd : change dir

-L	force symlinks to be followed



cp : copies files

-l	create symlink instead of physical copy

-v	see what actions are being taken


compress : zip up files

-v	show compression percentage



date : show current date & time

-u	UTC output


grep : regex based find util

-r	recursive searching


login : logs into the computer

-h	login to a specific host
-f 	login as another user


lp : prints to printer

-q	set job priority
-n	number of copies
-d	specify printer

        
ls : list contents of dir

-a      all files
-l      long format
-i      inode number


man : show user manual


mkdir : creates directory

-m      mode (chmod values)


more : paging utility

-s      squeeze multiple blank lines into 1
-p      pagnate not scroll


rm : remove files and or directories

-i      interactive prompt


rmdir : remove directories if empty

-p      remove specified parent directories as well


script : writes interactive commands to text file




------------------------------------------------------

1: Home directory
2: Script started, file is TT
3 - 18 : output from various commands given
19 : Script stopped, file is TT
20 : file 'TT' present in directory
21 : contents of previous interactive session logged into the file
